place.name: GIMINGHAM
place.gazetteerText: GIMINGHAM, a parish in Erpingham district. Norfolk; on the coast, 4 miles NNE of North Walsham r. station, 4 miles E of the line of telegraph from Norwich to Cromer, and 20 NNE of Norwich. Post town, Trunch, under Norwich. Acres, 1, 491; of which 20 are water. Real property, £2, 667. Pop., 332. Houses, 79. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £417.* Patron, Catherine Hall, Cambridge. The church is ancient but good; has an embattled tower; and contains a later English chest. Charities, "the bell-rope acre, " and a small piece of land held by the rector. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
